From Lake Bennett to the Bering Sea and across 2000 miles of wildlife, rough waters and more, former special forces operator and adventurer @jason_carl_fox and fellow adventurer Sean Johnson took on an epic unsupported expedition along the length of the Yukon River by Kayak. Learn more about their incredible journey in this video. #AboveAndBeyondStories

node.text:
Walking in the footsteps of 'Captain Scott’, @polarben set out to break the world record for the longest human-powered polar journey in history on a 1,795-mile trek to the South Pole while facing intense cold, altitude and weakened by half-rations. Learn about surviving on the edge in his video, and share your questions for Ben in his upcoming interview in the comments. #AboveAndBeyondStories
